### 6.6. Discussion on the \mathcal{C}^{1,\alpha} norm and its consequences

There are mainly two points that we want to insist upon in the definition of I\_{\alpha} in (7).

The first one is the fact that the supremum is taken over all couplings and not only over optimal couplings. As we mentioned above, the same choice/problem arises when defining the notion of derivative, and it has be shown in [16] that the two notions are equivalent. Of course, for I\_{\alpha}, one implies the other, but it is not clear for us to show an equivalence between the two notions and we leave this question for future research. In particular, the proof of [16] uses in a crucial manner the fact that the term we want to estimate can be seen as a part of a Taylor expansion, which is not true here.